caption: Fun salsa night with live band. $5-10 cover, good drinks, welcoming atmosphere
Great and fresh food, I liked the vibes the place has, and the workers were friendly. Will definitely come back in the future.
Feels like home.  Wonderful service.  Great food and drinks.  Music is always on point.  Love it.

I am a very polite and happy person, always having fun and spreading good vibes. It takes so much to get me triggered honestly and it am barely disrespectful to anyone. But this place really is one of the worst and the most shocking experiences I have ever had! I have never seen an owner of a business so rude to his customers. Unless you are not a person of color then you will receive a special treatment even no matter how much you spend and how respectful you are, you get treated like you are not welcomed in there  just for being a minority.
Excelent bar! Great music, Food and servers!
Bartenders are no good but the live music and people that go there to dance salsa were great.
Live Latin music and dancing on 1st floor! Second floor as well, less crowded... if that's what you need for cool down

I go to this great spot often! This is my favorite place to have a bite.  I visit this spot many times. The cooking is great, the team is courteous and the charge is reasonable. I like being in this place to have a rich meal.
Great place that serves good food and drinks! The music is always on point! I think that great pic show it all!
Live Salsa band was AMAZING!!
The cover charge is minimal, but the music the bands play are priceless!!!
Love this place! Great food and open mic sessions!
Had good music
Amazing place.
Great vibe with Brazilian decor, drinks, music, and cuisine!

Bossa was fantastic! The music is good, and upstairs they have a space for dancing and another bar. I went with my friend for her birthday, and we were easily able to host  30+ using the second story space.

The atmosphere is LOVELY the happy hour is awesome and there's always live music and dance after 9pm. Honestly you CANNOT go wrong with this place. It's very lounge-y during the day and I can't think of a better place to grab a good drink. DEFINITELY get a Caipirinha if you're here, they're to die for.
Delicious food and good people.

The music was fine but the service was not good. I was charged $7.67 for beers when their printed menu cited the charge as $6. When I asked about it, the staff initially replied that price was with the taxes and then later simply said that the menu did not reflect the prices correctly. They need to reprint their menus.

Brazilian music drinks and food. The place isn’t very big and they ask for cover entry . The service is good not a lot of tables or space in the bar. They have shows and dance upstairs. I’m a Brazilian so I’m happy having this corner in DC.
100% original Brazilian place....go go go
Snarky manager. Beware of the bald guy with glasses. Poor service and lousy drinks. However, Ambiance is nice.
Great place, great band & friendly crowd

Bossa is such a treat! I was intimidated at first, because I’ve never done salsa dancing but there are many advanced dancers willing to teach you and lead. This is a serious salsa bar, so don’t go expecting other types of music or dance. A really fun way to end the night!

Left a message on the reservation line and no one ever called me back. Arrived with friends to watch an early show, take a salsa lesson upstairs, and stay for dancing with live music. Our drinks were overly sweet and very weak and we had a hard time keeping drinks and food coming to the table. Eventually started ordering scotch neat from the bar.. overpriced. The upstairs space was entirely too small for a salsa class and overcrowded. We decided not to stay. The place has it's charm, but I'd also agree with what others have said here about the place being run down. The food was decent but I wouldn't go back simply because of the service - especially considering the price point of drinks.

Called their reservation line, no one answered. Called their main line to make a reservation, and the woman said "you can't make a reservation." When I asked if they're all booked tonight or if they don't take reservations, she hung up on me.  I was really excited to try this place tonight but I've never experienced such a rude call in my life. Clearly the service should be avoided at all costs.
Funny place, good food and nice people! They ussually have very good bands. I recomend it!

Great spot to go to. Live music and entertainment. Friendly staff. Parking is crazy but if you're willing to drive around for a few you'll definitely find parking, there is always someone leaving. The food was pretty good, it was suggested to me by the server. I enjoyed this spot.

Very lively venue with good music. Intimate atmosphere but not too overbearing. Good drinks and bartenders are prompt and courteous. The artworks on the wall are very nice and vivacious! Definitely plan on going again

I had very high expectations for this place. They play live salsa music on the bottom floor and some contemporary music on the top level. I was a little shocked at how small and run down the place was. There are pieces of broken wooden floor which is not safe to dance on. The windows were stained. There is no furniture on the top floor making the place look abandoned. Also, only one bathroom on the 2 floor. No safe place to put the coats. You can hang them at your own risk on he first floor. Drinks are reasonably priced, but I won't be back.

Food tasty good. However the price is high. You pay &12 for 8 slices of sausage, $6 for 6 thin slices of yuca. My husband and I went for dinner but we ended up going to the pizza next to it. Place is small end get crowded making it hard to walk around.

If you give the doorman money, you will never see it again, even if you're inside for less than one minute and find out it's not worth the cover charge. Don't give them your money! I know I'm never going back.
Love this place with Brazilian food, drinks and music

Great funky place, that draws a fun interesting cool crowd, Very chill place with music going, Brazilian food is fresh,and is good priced for being in DC and a great place to sit outside and "people watch". Great bands also
Salsa music amazing.
Awesome food, great mohitos and outstanding service!
Great live music tonight.

Super relaxing! Great, knowledgeable bartenders! Intriguing atmosphere! I love the idea of a downstairs in the basement dance floor even though it can get stuffy. The crowd is more on the younger side than mid thirties and older. Super sexy set up and lots of fun-if you're looking to have fun! ;))
Always been a fan if their Brushetta
Nice place for dance in Saturday and drink
Wonderful place. Food, drinks, music and service. Perfecto!

Nice bar with Latin music . Live salsa band around 10:30 pm on Saturdays.
One doorkeeper gives one price then an hour later the other door keeper gives a double price.

The second floor has no working air conditioning. Service is just average.

Great latin dance in Adams Morgan
Great place for Brazilian food and drinks, cool vibe, excellent world music.
Great ambiance; excellent music. Must visit if you are looking for a fun night weekday or weekend while in DC. We plan to go again.

Cozy place, arts all around you, great atmosphere, had delicious food (shrimp + Salad) for $24 , it was Saturday, they had live music, two bands, once finished around 8:30pm the other started around 10:40pm, Ok I am not bachata or salsa dancer, went there with no partner, but I found a space to dance and have fun with my self, as usual 😍 Ok I don’t drink so I can’t tell you about drinks there, also don’t expect a huge menu of food, what you saw in pictures here you will see around you with people if you go there.
Wonderful place!! And the food is one of the best of DC!
Guy at the front tried to up the cover charge from $5 to $10 when our bigger group arrived. Then the minimum credit card charge for drinks is $15. Absolutely nonsense.
Drinks are strong 💪
Always a great dining experience. After dinner hours brings live Latin music for dancing--a super and well-established venue in Adams Morgan.

They deny you water! . They want to sell you bottled water, and if they ran out they won't give tap water. I honestly think that this practice is extremely dangerous and will cause alcohol intoxication a real problem. So be careful....
Cozy place that always has interesting gigs
Don't underestimate the food here - delicious and not what you would expect for the Adams Morgan bar scene.
Loved the ambiance and the foods taste awesome.

I went here after hours. It didn't seem like a Bistro, it was a night club at this point. It was fun though the music wasn't entirely great. They had Salsa on one floor and electronic in the second floor. Songs of both genres were pretty specific, which could be good if you're really into them. The people dancing salsa were really experts. The bar had really good drinks but their beer selection wasn't really good.

Live music there is almost always wonderful. Definitely super crowded dance/salsa floor but better than others in the area & what good one isn't? Upstairs is great if you are with friends, but comparatively poor music usually.
I love it

live music is great
Nice music and food!

This Is the place. Brazilian, Spanish love music. Great tapas. Wagner the owner great person. Love this place
I really love the music at Bossa, lack of seating to make room for dancing is a plus and a minus.  Hard to get a drink at times, AC hardly works, but the dancing is fantastic!
Great music and staff. Could use a little tlc. Worth checking who's playing if you're in the area
Amazing! Friendly staff and YUMMY food and drinks. Oh and amazing music in a relaxed environment.
Loved the live music , their Brazilian beer was 2 box on happy hour ....
Awesome music and ethnic foods

Loved it!  the live salsa band was amazing! this place has a nice-relaxed vibe.  Loved the decoration.  Mojitos and food were great! they have DJ upstairs and even Bachata class :-)  the only thing was the AC.. it got super humid downstairs when everybody was dancing.
Good place for salsa dance lovers, they also have a bar upstairs.
Great music, super friendly staff and good company.
Great live music!
Went there for live music night nice crowd and friendly bartenders but kind of small and crowded...not bad if you like small spaces.
Love this place. Great music, great food, great ambience.
Nice chill environment with good live music

You like Salsa? You like live music? You want to practice your Spanish while experiencing both of those things? Go here. It's easily accessible in DC and has the best Salsa/live music scene in the district.
warm bartenders!
It is a great venue for music with cheap tickets, many times free entrance. Food is a little on the expensive side and the portions are small. Happy hours tropical cocktails for $5.
Salsaaaaa. Live music on Fridays

I love this place. Great live salsa on Friday nights downstairs. Not so busy that you can't find a place to dance. There are a good variety of dancers at a variety of skill levels and its got a good positive and non-judgemental vibe. Great intimate place to take a girl for a night of dancing. Super cozy. Live music and intimate. The nights I went the bands played exclusively salsa with maybe a guest singer at times.
Awesome BraSilian bar food. Great cachaça too!
My fav place on Tuesdays, they have some great live music

Cocktails are mediocre but very atmospheric place! When we were there almost all other people inside looked like Brazilians and some band was performing live Brazilian music - we will be back for sure!
Love it!! Amazing food Awesome music.  Thank You

I had my birthday celebration this year at Bossa Bistro & Lounge, and had a blast. It was on a Friday night and was full to capacity.  It started off a little rough from a hospitality stance, but as time progressed the customer service had gotten better. The band was AMAZING and very interactive with the guest. My family and friends had a ball.  We will definitely come back to Bossa again!
Food is good
Tapas were good, recommends the meatballs and yucca. The mojitos are pretty good for happy hour as well. Service is VERY slow.
